\U2022 What Is Rssp?\N\U2022 What Can Rssp Do?\N\U2022 What Makes Rssp Better Than Username And Password?\N\U2022 Does Rssp Use And Store My Existing Usernames And Passwords?\N\U2022 What Is Required To Use Rssp?\N\U2022 What Services Can I Link To Rssp?\N\U2022 What Browsers Does Rssp Support?\N\U2022 Didn\'T Find What You Were Looking For?

Rssp Is A Global Security Service Providing Sign In And Online Transaction Security For Online Services. End Users Use The Service With Rssp Keys, Which Comes As A Smartphone App Or A Usb Key. The Users Can Manage Their Rssp Keys Using The Rssp Website. Rssp User Can Have Multiple Rssp Apps And Keys On His Account, And Lock Lost Apps And Keys To Prevent Misuse. Some Services Might Integrate Rssp Keys Into Their Own Apps Or Provide Branded Usb Keys.

Rssp Can Prevent Unauthorized Use Of Usernames And Passwords. The So Called 2-Step Verification Or 2-Factor Authentication Verifies The User During Login. Similarly Rssp Can Prevent Unauthorized Transactions Or User Account Changes By Verifying The User Real-Time When Transactions Happen. Some Services Also Allow Their Users To Use Rssp To Sign In Without Passwords At All, Providing The Greatest Level Of User Convenience.\Nthe Service Providers Can Select Their Own Policies And Offer The User Verification Operations Like:\N \U2022 Verify User When They Sign In From New Ip Or Device\N \U2022 Verify User When They Change Their Account\N \U2022 Verify User Every Time They Login\N \U2022 Verify Transactions (Purchase, Sell, Trade, Etc)\N \U2022 Allow Login Without A Password\N \U2022 Allow Easy New User Registration With Rssp
What Makes Rssp Better Than Username And Password?

Usernames And Passwords Are Hard To Manage, Insecure And There\'S Just Too Many Of Them. Single Sign-On Services Based On Username And Password Don\'T Really Fix The Security Issues. Storing Your Usernames And Passwords Into A Central Storage Still Leaves You Vulnerable To The Phishing Attacks.\Nrssp Does Not Use Or Store Usernames And Passwords. We Believe That Any Solution Based On Usernames And Passwords Is Obsolete, Difficult To Use And Too Easy To Break.\Nrssp Is Based On Public Key Infrastructure (Pki). This Is A Similar System Which Governments And Big Enterprises Use To Maximize Secure Authentication Of Their Closed Services. Rssp Does The Same In The Public Internet.\Nrssp Makes Passwords Obsolete. Each Rssp App Has A Private Key Identifying The Device. You Control The Access To The App With Your Chosen Pin Code. You Are Authenticated With Something You Have And With The One Optional Secret You Remember. If Your Rssp Device Is Lost Or Stolen, Lock The App At Rssp Website.
Does Rssp Use And Store My Existing Usernames And Passwords?
No, Rssp Does Not Use Or Store Any Of Your Usernames And Passwords. Further, Rssp Itself Does Not Require Username And Password. Rssp Stands For Zero Passwords.
What Is Required To Use Rssp?
Rssp App Is Available For Ios And Android Devices. You Don\'T Need Any Specific Software For The Pc Or Mac.\Nsince We Do Not Rely On Usernames And Passwords, Even Public Computers Can Be Used Safely.
What Services Can I Link To Rssp?
Rssp Works With Services Who Integrate To Our Backend. Those Services Typically Promote Rssp At Their Login Page And In The User Settings, Where The Actual Linking Of Your Rssp Key Takes Place.

Rssp Supports The Following Browsers:\N \U2022 Windows Os:\N \U2022 Ie9+\N \U2022 Firefox Latest Releases\N \U2022 Chrome Latest Releases\N \U2022 Safari Latest Releases\N \U2022 Mac Os X:\N \U2022 Firefox Latest Releases\N \U2022 Chrome Latest Releases\N \U2022 Safari Latest Releases\N \U2022 We Also Have A Limited, Alpha Stage Support For Certain Linux Distributions.

Mobile-Id Is An Authentication And Authorization Service, Enabling The End-Users To Authenticate Themselves To Multiple Internet Services In A Secure Manner. A Usb Peripheral ("Rssp Key") Or A Client Software Program, Activated By A User And Device Specific Pin Code, Is Used By End-Users To Manage Their Accounts In A Centralized But Secure Manner.\N\Nno Disclosure Of Personal Data Of Any Kind (Such As Name, Age, Location, Face Data) Is Necessary To Use Mobile-Id When The Service Is Only Used To Manage End-User\'S Access Credentials For Internet Services. The End-User\'S Username And Password Information Related To An Internet Service Are Not Stored In Mobile-Id Although A List Of The Internet Services Accessible By Certain Rssp Account Is Stored. When Mobile-Id Is Used In The Manner Described Above, The Information Concerning Rssp Keys Or Accounts Cannot Be Directly Linked To Any Particular Person.\N\Nmobile-Id Provides End-Users An Option To Store Personal Data In Their Rssp Keys And Software Clients. End-Users May Store Personal Data That May Be Necessary For Using Some Internet Services, For Example To Verify To An Internet Service That The End-User Is Of A Certain Age. All Personal Data Disclosed By An End-User Is Stored Permanently Only In The End-User\'S Rssp Key Or Software Client And Is Disclosed To An Internet Service Only Upon A Query From The Service And Only With An Express Consent Of The End-User For Each Query Separately. Temporary Processing Of The End-User\'S Personal Data By Mobile-Id Is Necessary When The End-User Discloses Or Edits The Personal Data Stored In The Rssp Key Or Software Client, Or When End-User Data Is Disclosed To An Internet Service. The Data Is Always Discarded Without Delay After Being Processed And Is Not Stored By Mobile-Id In Any Other Place Than The End-User\'S Rssp Key Or Software Client.\N\Nan End-User May Choose To Disclose Optional Personal Data (Such As An E-Mail Address Or A Phone Number) To Be Used By Mobile-Id For The Purposes Of Communication Between The End-User And Mobile-Id.\N\Nany Data Concerning The Use By A Specific End-User Of Different Internet Services Via Mobile-Id May Only Be Stored In And Used By Mobile-Id Or Mobile-Id™ For The Purpose Of Fraud Detection Or Other Similar Purposes, And To Compile An End-User Specific Trust Index Which It May Provide To Third Parties Upon Their Request Without Obtaining A Separate Consent From The End-User. The Trust Index Is Only A Technical Attribute Which Cannot Be Reduced To Personal Information Relating To Any Private Person.\N\Npersonal End-User Data Stored In Mobile-Id May Be Transferred Within Mobile-Id To Any Server In Any Country Worldwide. Mobile-Id™ Always Protects Any Personal Data By Using Adequate Data Security Procedures And Technologies. The Core Principle Of Mobile-Id Is To Store All Personal Data (Except Of The Above Mentioned Optional Contact Information) In A Decentralized Manner Into The Rssp Keys And/Or Software Clients, Which Are At The Sole Possession And Control Of The End-Users Themselves. Thus The Protection By Each End-User Of The Rssp Key Or Software Client And The Associated Pin Code Is The Key Aspect Of The Protection Of The Personal Data Stored In Mobile-Id. If A Rssp Key Or A Device With Rssp Client Software Is Lost By An End-User, The End-User\'S Personal Data May Be At Risk, And Cannot Be Recovered By Mobile-Id™. It Is Essential That End-User Has A Copy Of Her Unlock Code, Which Can Be Used To Revoke And Lock Lost Rssp Key Or Software Client. Mobile-Id™ Is Not Responsible For End-Users\' Data Or The Authenticity Thereof In Any Way, Except That Mobile-Id™ Undertakes To Use Adequate Data Security Procedures And Technologies During The Processing Of The End-Users\' Data. Mobile-Id™ Shall Not Be Liable For Any Damages Caused By Inaccurate End-User Data Or The Loss Of Any End-User Data.\N\Nmobile-Id™ Shall Not Use, Store Or Disclose The End-User\'S Personal Data In Any Other Manner Than What Has Been Described Herein Without The Consent Of The End-User. Any Personal Data Disclosed To Mobile-Id That Is Not Automatically Destroyed Immediately After Processing Shall Be Destroyed Without Undue Delay After The End-User Finally Ceases To Use Mobile-Id. The End-User Is Responsible For Destroying Data Stored In The Rssp Key Or Software Clients.\N\Nan End-User Shall Hereby Expressly Consent To The Collection And Processing Of Personal Data Before Using Mobile-Id. Consent To Collect And Process Personal Data May Be Revoked By The End-User At Any Time, But Use Of Mobile-Id Must Be Discontinued After Such Revocation. An End-User May Inspect And Amend The Personal Data Stored Into Mobile-Id At Any Time By Using Tools Provided At Mobile-Id Web Site Or By Using The Contact Information Below.
